%N A397452 Number of partitions of n into two 5-smooth numbers.
%C A397452 The two 5-smooth numbers can be equal.
%e A397452 a(7) = 3 because 7 has 3 ways to be written as two 5-smooth numbers: 7 = 6 + 1 = 5 + 2 = 4 + 3 where 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, and 6 are all 5-smooth numbers.
%o A397452 (PARI)
%o A397452 is_A051037(n)=m=n; forprime(p=2, 5, while(m%p==0, m=m/p)); return(m==1)
%o A397452 A397452(n)=sum(k=1, n/2, is_A051037(k*(n-k)))
%Y A397452 Cf. A051037, A112581, A394249.
%K A397452 nonn
%O A397452 1,4
